Welcome to the Paris Hotel. As you navigate, most things you encounter can be interacted with in some way. If one verb doesn't work, try another! You can also LOOK at things, scenery, and even yourself! Try it out!

You are in the taxi drop.

Even though the taxi ride wasn't long, the Nevada heat punches you in the face. Much more arrid than the Florida humidity you're used to.

You can go north.

> n

> n

You are in a lobby.

As you walk into the hotel you are immediately transported to France! The ceiling is painted to look like the sky and the Eiffel Tower that can be seen from outside cuts into the hotel and can be accessed from within. There is traditional French music playing over the intercoms, and the surrounding area is certainly smokey like Paris.

You can go north, south, east or west.

> n

> n

You are in a casino.

There is quite an assortment of gambling opportunities in this first casino area.

You can see slot machines, a black jack table and a keno station.

You can go north, south, east or west.

> x slot machines

> x slot machines
Slot machines! Well these are a cheap and easy way to lose all of your money...
There are three slot machines in the following themes: Journey, Backstreet Boys and John Mayer.
> x journey

> x journey
A Journey themed slot machine blasting "Don't Stop Believing."
You can see a gold lever.
> pull gold lever

> pull gold lever
The wheels spin and click into place... YOU WON! A voucher prints out for you to take.
> take voucher

> take voucher
You add the voucher to your inventory.
